{
  "local_port": 42726,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some mind-blowing tech tools that most people don't know about?",
  "response": "There are numerous innovative tech tools that can significantly enhance productivity, creativity, or convenience, yet many people remain unaware of them. Here are some mind-blowing tech tools that are not as widely known:\n\n### 1. **Notion** *(Productivity/Organization)*\n   - An all-in-one workspace that combines notes, tasks, databases, and project management. It\u2019s highly customizable and can replace multiple apps like Evernote, Trello, and Google Docs.\n\n### 2. **Obsidian** *(Note-Taking/Knowledge Management)*\n   - A powerful Markdown-based note-taking tool that allows you to create a \"second brain.\" It uses bi-directional linking to connect ideas, making it ideal for building knowledge systems.\n\n### 3. **Raycast** *(Productivity/Shortcut Tool)*\n   - A fast and customizable launcher for macOS that goes beyond Spotlight. It allows you to control apps, run scripts, and automate workflows with extensions.\n\n### 4. **Houdini** *(3D Animation/VFX)*\n   - A professional-grade tool for 3D animation, visual effects, and procedural modeling. While it\u2019s widely used in Hollywood, it\u2019s not as well-known outside the VFX industry.\n\n### 5. **Runway ML** *(AI/Content Creation)*\n   - A suite of AI-powered tools for video editing, image generation, and creative projects. It democratizes access to machine learning for artists and creators.\n\n### 6. **FigJam** *(Collaboration/Brainstorming)*\n   - A collaborative whiteboarding tool from Figma, perfect for teams to brainstorm, sketch ideas, and create diagrams in real time.\n\n### 7. **Excalidraw** *(Drawing/Diagramming)*\n   - A simple, open-source tool for creating hand-drawn diagrams and sketches. It\u2019s great for brainstorming, flowcharts, and wireframes.\n\n### 8. **DeepL** *(Language Translation)*\n   - A translation tool that often outperforms Google Translate in accuracy and natural-sounding translations, especially for complex sentences.\n\n### 9. **NotebookLM (formerly Project Tailwind)** *(AI/Knowledge Management)*\n   - An AI-powered tool by Google that organizes and summarizes your notes and documents, making it easier to extract insights and connections.\n\n### 10. **Luna Display** *(Hardware/Productivity)*\n   - A hardware dongle that turns an iPad or another Mac into a wireless second display. It\u2019s a great alternative to purely software-based solutions.\n\n### 11. **Tana** *(Knowledge Management/Productivity)*\n   - A supercharged note-taking and organization tool that combines elements of Notion and Roam Research, with a focus on AI-assisted workflows.\n\n### 12. **Coda** *(Document Automation/Productivity)*\n   - A hybrid of documents and spreadsheets that allows you to create interactive, data-driven documents with built-in automation.\n\n### 13. **Krita** *(Digital Art)*\n   - A free, open-source digital painting program that rivals paid tools like Photoshop. It\u2019s packed with features for artists and illustrators.\n\n### 14. **Otter.ai** *(Audio Transcription/AI)*\n   - A tool that provides real-time transcription for meetings, interviews, and lectures. It\u2019s highly accurate and supports collaboration.\n\n### 15. **Loom** *(Video Messaging/Collaboration)*\n   - A tool for recording and sharing video messages, ideal for asynchronous communication, tutorials, or feedback.\n\n### 16. **Birch** *(AI/Writing)*\n   - A minimalist AI writing tool that focuses on simplicity and distraction-free writing, perfect for authors and content creators.\n\n### 17. **Whimsical** *(Visual Collaboration)*\n   - A tool for creating flowcharts, wireframes, and mind maps quickly and collaboratively. It\u2019s intuitive and great for team projects.\n\n### 18. **Descript** *(Audio/Video Editing)*\n   - An innovative tool for editing audio and video by editing the transcript. It\u2019s like word processing for media files.\n\n### 19. **Zapier** *(Automation)*\n   - Automates workflows between apps and services, saving time by connecting tools like Gmail, Slack, and Trello without coding.\n\n### 20. **Superhuman** *(Email Management)*\n   - A premium email client designed for speed and efficiency, with keyboard shortcuts and AI-powered features to help you achieve \"inbox zero.\"\n\nThese tools can transform how you work, create, and organize, yet many people haven\u2019t discovered them yet. Give them a try and see which ones fit your workflow!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
